thread.title: Prep Volleyball: Battle ends Lady Jays' season

author: News Tribune
title: Prep Volleyball: Battle ends Lady Jays' season
text:
Share 
The Jefferson City Lady Jays fell in the district semifinals to the Battle Spartans at Troy Buchanan High School on Tuesday night. 
Following a 2-1 win Monday against Rock Bridge in the first round of the Class 4 District 9 tournament, the Lady Jays’ season came to an end with a 25-18, 25-22 loss to Battle. 
Mary Wehmeyer led the team in kills with eight, while recording six digs and seven service points. Janice Steacy had 13 assists, five digs, 10 service points and a kill. Bailey Diehl had five assists, three digs and four service points. Baylee Rozier had nine digs, three kills and nine service points. 
Megan Bleidistel served up six points and had five digs. Tatum Gaines recorded four kills, three blocks, one dig and five service points. Cameryn Campbell had nine digs, while Maddi Stone had two. Corrin Lepper had one kill and a block. Cara Caby had two kills. 
Jefferson City ends its season at 13-19-1. ﻿
